quran[26]{c,v,t,f}:
56,51,"Then you, the erring ones and those that gave the lie to the Truth,"
56,52,"shall all eat from the Tree of al-Zaqqum, {1}",footnotes:1:For the explanation of zaqqum
56,53,"filling your bellies with it;"
56,54,"and thereupon you shall drink boiling water,"
56,55,"drinking it as thirsty camels do.”"
56,56,"Thus shall they be entertained on the Day of Recompense."
56,57,"We have created you, {1} then why would you not confirm it? {2}",footnotes:1:The arguments from here to verse 74 provide the reasoning to prove both the doctrines of Tauhid and of Hereafter rationally. For it was there two basic doctrines of the Prophet’s (peace be upon him) teaching that the people of Makkah were debating and objecting to at that time.That is
56,58,"Did you ever consider the sperm that you emit?"
56,59,"Do you create a child out of it, or are We its creators? {1}",footnotes:1:In this brief sentence a very important question has been put before man. Apart from all other things in the world
56,60,"It is We Who ordained death upon you {1} and We are not to be frustrated.",footnotes:1:That is
56,61,"Had We so wished, nothing could have hindered Us from replacing you by others like yourselves, or transforming you into beings you know nothing about. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
56,62,"You are well aware of the first creation; then, do you learn no lesson from it? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
56,63,"Have you considered the seeds you till?"
56,64,"Is it you or We Who make them grow? {1}",footnotes:1:The above question drew the people’s attention to the truth that they have been developed and nourished by Allah Almighty and have come into being by His act of creation. Now this second question draws their attention to this important truth that the provisions which sustain them are also created only by Allah for them
56,65,"If We so wished, We could have reduced your harvest to rubble, and you would have been left wonder-struck to exclaim:"
56,66,"“We have been penalised;"
56,67,"nay; we have been undone!”"
56,68,"Did you cast a good look at the water that you drink?"
56,69,"Is it you who brought it down from the clouds or is it We Who brought it down? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
56,70,"If We had so pleased, We could have made it bitter. {1} So why would you not give thanks? {2}",footnotes:1:In other words
56,71,"Did you consider the fire which you kindle?"
56,72,"Did you make its tree {1} grow or was it We Who made it grow?",footnotes:1:The tree here either implies the tree that supplies wood for lighting a fire
56,73,"We made it a reminder {1} and a provision for the needy. {2}",footnotes:1:Making the fire a means of remembrance means: The fire by virtue of its quality of being kindled at all times reminds man of his forgotten lesson that without it human life could not be any different from animal life. Because of the fire only did man learn to cook food for eating instead of eating it raw like the animals
56,74,"Glorify, then, (O Prophet), the name of your Great Lord. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
56,75,"No! {1} I swear by the positions of the stars –",footnotes:1:That is
56,76,"and this is indeed a mighty oath, if only you knew –"
